snippet.textDisplay: The term, "Greyhounds" is a term also used for a naval Destroyer...or "Tin Can" ....I was a Tin Can sailor....not during this time, but during the "Cold War" I was a Gunners Mate, so I love to see those 5"/.38 guns firing. On this trailer I see mostly single mounts. I was on  DD 824 ..USS Basilone. that was twin mounts, and USS Voge, FF 1047, a single mount, much like these. I know rough seas and have been in many. These guys had it tough, they were tough as nails sailors. The Merchant Marines had it tougher tho. Looks like a lot of computer generated scenes. Might be a good movie.
